        "\n",
        "  CalibrationDisplay.from_estimator(\n",
        "      estimator = estimator,\n",
        "      X = X_test,\n",
        "      y = y_test,\n",
        "      n_bins = 20,\n",
        "      name = name,\n",
        "      color = color,\n",
        "      ax = ax\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    \n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Calibration Plot (Test Set)\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "calibration-s2-test",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "The uncalibrated CatBoost model shows **better** calibration than the calibrated model. This is likely due to the isotonic regression model overfitting to the tuning set. We will use the uncalibrated model to set the optimal decision threshold.\n",
        "\n",
        "Evalulate the original decision threshold of 0.5 on the test set."
      ],
      "id": "7c36dd21"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: evaluate-default-threshold-s2\n",
        "\n",
        "leaderboard_s2_default = ag_model_s2_predictor.leaderboard(\n",
        "    df_test_ft.to_pandas()\n",
        "    , extra_metrics=['f1']\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "display(leaderboard_s2_default)"
      ],
      "id": "evaluate-default-threshold-s2",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Since the tuning set is no longer being used for probability calibration, we will use it to find the optimal decision threshold that maximizes the F1-score."
      ],
      "id": "59d2f38b"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: threshold-tuning-s2\n",
        "\n",
        "best_threshold_s2 = (ag_model_s2_predictor\n",
        "                .calibrate_decision_threshold(\n",
        "                data = df_tuning_ft.to_pandas(),\n",
        "                metric = 'f1',\n",
        "                decision_thresholds = 200)\n",
        "                )\n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model_s2_predictor.set_decision_threshold(best_threshold_s2)\n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model_s2_predictor.save()  # Save the predictor with the new threshold"
      ],
      "id": "threshold-tuning-s2",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
