    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Tuning the decision threshold does not appear to substantially improve the F1-score on the test set. The default threshold of 0.5 yields a similar F1-score.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Cost-Sensitive Learning Approach\n",
        "\n",
        "**Concept Recap:** Cost-sensitive learning is achieved by assigning higher weights to the minority class (fraud) instances during training. AutoGluon handles this internally when `sample_weight='balance_weight'` is specified. We will use `average_precision` as the evaluation metric.\n",
        "\n",
        "Setup AutoGluon parameters."
      ],
      "id": "df7e6c8a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: setup-autogluon-cost-sensitive\n",
        "\n",
        "strategy_name_3 = \"3. Cost Sensitive Learning\"\n",
        "model_folder_s3 = \"./Lab04_ag_models_s3_cost_sensitive\"\n",
        "remove_ag_folder(model_folder_s3)\n",
        "\n",
        "predictor_args_s3 = {\n",
        "    'problem_type': 'binary',\n",
        "    'eval_metric': 'average_precision', \n",
        "    'path': model_folder_s3,\n",
        "    'sample_weight': 'balance_weight' # Use balance weights for cost-sensitive learning\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "fit_args_s3 = {'holdout_frac': 0.2,\n",
        "            'excluded_model_types': ['KNN'],\n",
        "            'presets': 'medium_quality',\n",
        "            'time_limit': 180}  \n",
        "\n",
        "ag_wrapper_s3 = AutoGluonSklearnWrapper(\n",
        "    label=target_label,\n",
        "    predictor_args=predictor_args_s3,\n",
        "    fit_args=fit_args_s3,\n",
        "    n_jobs=num_jobs\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "id": "setup-autogluon-cost-sensitive",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Fit the model using AutoGluon."
      ],
      "id": "f024c919"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "ag_model_s3 = ag_wrapper_s3.fit(X_train, y_train) \n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model_s3.predictor.save()  # Save the predictor for later use"
      ],
      "id": "bdeecebb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
